(Tharn)

00:10:40.400 --> 00:10:42.800
Phaya, did you tell your sister and grandma...

00:10:42.800 --> 00:10:44.800
when you left the hospital last night?

00:10:45.480 --> 00:10:46.280
No.

00:10:47.920 --> 00:10:50.040
Did you call them this morning?

00:10:51.800 --> 00:10:54.120
Shit, I forgot.

00:10:56.680 --> 00:10:58.080
I didn’t bring my phone with me.

00:10:59.960 --> 00:11:03.840
Yai, Grandma, and your sister are looking for you right now.

00:11:08.240 --> 00:11:11.840
Tharn! Tharn! Open the door!

00:11:11.920 --> 00:11:14.000
Tharn! Tharn!

00:11:15.760 --> 00:11:17.520
Phaya has been missing since last night.

00:11:17.800 --> 00:11:19.400
His grandma and sister are looking for him.

00:11:21.400 --> 00:11:24.800
Tharn! Phaya has been missing from the hospital since last night.

00:11:24.800 --> 00:11:26.320
I still couldn’t contact him.

00:11:26.320 --> 00:11:28.920
Do you know where he is?

00:11:30.600 --> 00:11:31.360
Do you?

00:11:31.480 --> 00:11:33.680
Umm, I’m here, Grandma.

00:11:55.760 --> 00:11:57.200
Please drink some water first, Grandma.

00:12:05.520 --> 00:12:07.240
You’ve just recovered.

00:12:07.560 --> 00:12:09.760
Why did you rush out of the hopsital like that? Why did you run away?

00:12:09.800 --> 00:12:11.320
Why did you run away?

00:12:11.640 --> 00:12:15.200
Do you know your sister and I were worried sick about you?

00:12:18.480 --> 00:12:19.840
I’m really sorry, Grandma.

00:12:21.600 --> 00:12:22.480
I just...

00:12:23.680 --> 00:12:26.080
had an urgent case to discuss with Tharn.

00:12:28.680 --> 00:12:31.640
Where did you discuss it, on the bed or sofa?

00:12:35.160 --> 00:12:38.000
You shouldn’t care about your work more than your care for your life.

00:12:38.800 --> 00:12:42.480
Didn’t you know you almost got killed from drowning?

00:12:43.240 --> 00:12:45.520
Grandma and I were so worried about you.

00:12:48.040 --> 00:12:51.080
I’m really sorry for not thinking it through.

00:12:51.360 --> 00:12:53.240
I’m sorry I didn’t tell you and Nee first.

00:12:54.600 --> 00:12:55.760
I’m really sorry.

00:13:04.360 --> 00:13:07.160
I have to apologize to Grandma and Paranee too...

00:13:07.520 --> 00:13:12.760
for not telling you when I found out he had left the hospital last night. I should have called and let you know.

00:13:27.760 --> 00:13:31.760
Grandma, I’m sorry for making you worried.

00:13:34.680 --> 00:13:38.040
I promise I’ll be more careful from now on.

00:13:39.280 --> 00:13:41.320
I will always think twice and not act on impulse.

00:13:42.440 --> 00:13:45.360
And I will not do anything that’d make you and Nee...

00:13:46.920 --> 00:13:48.440
worry about me again.

00:13:55.480 --> 00:13:57.320
Please rest assured, Grandma.

00:13:58.480 --> 00:14:00.600
I’ll help take care of him too.

00:14:07.720 --> 00:14:09.680
Hey.

00:14:10.320 --> 00:14:11.440
Why are you holding hands?

00:14:12.600 --> 00:14:13.680
Are you guys lovers?

00:14:14.680 --> 00:14:15.840
Really?

00:14:16.640 --> 00:14:17.880
Since when?

00:14:18.280 --> 00:14:21.560
Why didn’t anyone tell me that you guys are together?

00:14:24.080 --> 00:14:25.400
So fake, Yai.

00:14:30.080 --> 00:14:31.640
Grandma.

00:14:32.360 --> 00:14:34.120
I have something important to tell you.

00:14:43.160 --> 00:14:44.160
Give me a second.

00:14:48.960 --> 00:14:49.960
Okay, go ahead.

00:14:53.960 --> 00:14:54.760
Well...

00:14:56.400 --> 00:14:57.840
Tharn and I,

00:15:00.400 --> 00:15:01.760
we are...

00:15:04.240 --> 00:15:05.400
we’re dating.

00:15:10.640 --> 00:15:11.520
Give me a second.

00:15:18.920 --> 00:15:23.720
So, if it weren’t because you ran out of the hospital last night...

00:15:23.720 --> 00:15:25.720
and then I finally found you here,

00:15:26.760 --> 00:15:29.040
you’d have still kept it a secret from me, wouldn’t you?

00:15:29.160 --> 00:15:33.000
I didn’t mean to keep it a secret from you, Grandma.

00:15:33.160 --> 00:15:35.400
I just didn’t get a chance to tell you.

00:15:35.920 --> 00:15:37.880
I was afraid you might not approve of...

00:15:38.880 --> 00:15:40.080
me dating a guy.

00:15:47.200 --> 00:15:48.200
Phaya.

00:15:49.080 --> 00:15:51.000
Haven’t I told you before...

00:15:52.720 --> 00:15:56.840
that whom you want to be with is your own choice to make?

00:15:57.200 --> 00:15:59.440
Because it’s you who’d live that life.

00:16:00.760 --> 00:16:02.040
Don’t you remember?

00:16:05.120 --> 00:16:06.040
Tharn.

00:16:06.560 --> 00:16:11.920
Thank you for always taking care of him.

00:16:12.160 --> 00:16:14.400
Since that day when he was drowned...

00:16:15.320 --> 00:16:18.400
and recently when you had brought him back from death.

00:16:19.920 --> 00:16:24.360
If it weren’t because of you,

00:16:28.040 --> 00:16:31.480
I would have lost him long ago.

00:16:32.440 --> 00:16:33.560
Thank you, dear.

00:16:35.040 --> 00:16:37.160
Thank you for understanding me, Grandma.

00:16:41.360 --> 00:16:43.240
Please don’t worry, Grandma.

00:16:43.640 --> 00:16:45.240
It is my job to protect him.

00:16:46.320 --> 00:16:48.360
I will always be by his side.

00:17:09.640 --> 00:17:13.960
You go on and talk to them.

00:17:30.760 --> 00:17:31.680
Grandma.

00:17:32.360 --> 00:17:33.080
Yes?

00:17:36.040 --> 00:17:37.320
There’s one more thing.

00:17:38.880 --> 00:17:40.120
Oh, more?

00:17:42.600 --> 00:17:44.120
Give me a second.

00:17:50.040 --> 00:17:51.040
Now you can say it.

00:17:51.840 --> 00:17:52.720
Well...

00:17:53.720 --> 00:17:55.720
during this time that I’m still recovering,

00:17:56.600 --> 00:17:59.040
Tharn has to go back to Nongkai.

00:17:59.960 --> 00:18:03.400
Can I...can I go with him too?

00:18:03.960 --> 00:18:06.080
So that we could take care of each other.

00:18:06.520 --> 00:18:10.680
Awww, you’re so crazy in love, Police Officer.

00:18:13.840 --> 00:18:15.960
Is that all?

00:18:16.880 --> 00:18:18.880
You scared me.

00:18:19.080 --> 00:18:20.880
You don’t have to ask for my permission.

00:18:21.560 --> 00:18:24.280
After that drowning incident,

00:18:25.080 --> 00:18:27.320
I still haven’t gone back to Nongkai since then.

00:18:29.080 --> 00:18:32.720
Can I go with you? I want to go see the Abbot too.

00:18:32.960 --> 00:18:33.880
Can I?

00:18:34.160 --> 00:18:35.240
Of course, Grandma.

00:18:40.280 --> 00:18:42.080
Thank you, Grandma.

00:18:55.200 --> 00:18:59.000
Inspector, we’ve found a suspect. Do you want our team to arrest him?

00:18:59.040 --> 00:18:59.880
Not yet.

00:19:00.000 --> 00:19:02.280
Tell them to keep an eye on our suspect.

00:19:03.880 --> 00:19:07.960
Hey, we must get as much infromation as possible today.

00:19:08.160 --> 00:19:09.040
Singh

00:19:10.080 --> 00:19:12.840
Can you hack into the police bureau database?

00:19:13.520 --> 00:19:17.760
I want to know what Chart has been doing since he left the training camp.

00:19:17.760 --> 00:19:19.240
You got it. I’ll take care of that.

00:19:19.560 --> 00:19:20.640
And for me...

00:19:21.200 --> 00:19:22.680
I’ll go check out the Inspector’s desk.

00:19:23.560 --> 00:19:25.200
He might hide something in there.

00:19:26.040 --> 00:19:26.760
Let’s go.

00:19:28.080 --> 00:19:33.560
